I don't even know how to start to describe this place... Everyone I talked to said we had to go and check it out, especially if we liked beer and people watching. This place definitely fit the bill!  To begin, this place is a literal market. More of a bodega really. You walk in to a small snack shop. They have local cheeses and meats and jar items. And chips, and t-shirts, and cigarettes. If you turn right there is a deli in the next room. There's a cooler with premade sandwiches, salads, pastas, cheeses, etc. And they have vegetarian and vegan items aplenty in there. There is also a random vending machine for musicians with drum sticks and stringed instrument strings.  If you continue straight when you walk in past the bathrooms on the left and the register on the right, you'll come to a small 6 stool bar on your left with 15-20 beer taps and a lot of wine options. They also had canned and bottled beer. In fact you can peruse the extensive beer section at the back of the store and drink it thee if you'd like! There's also a few tables and chairs to sit at, but not a whole lot. You can also drink out on their front patio, that has heaters when it's cold.  This was just a very interesting place to spend an hour at on a Saturday night. But it was fun and the beer was delicious and the company friendly. I'd stop back in Everytime I'm in the area!

The majority of the employees at common market are friendly and outgoing. But one particular employee has a history of being antagonistic. This employee in question is responsible for the supervision of the front patio. Every time I visit this establishment, he initiates an altercation with me for some reason. One night I was defending a dog getting kicked by a belligerent drunk who kept irritating other customers, and he yelled at me telling me he would kick me out if I kept talking to this guy. Recently a female friend dropped a glass by accident and he came over (once he finished on his phone) to yell at her and tell her she was drunk (which she was not) and if she kept it up, that she would be kicked out. Meanwhile, minutes after I complained to the manager... who did absolutely nothing to fix the situation or even acknowledge it.. a male at a nearby table broke his glass and provoked a very different response from this employee. Rather than react aggressively he instead treated the incident with a complete lack of concern. Then afterward was seen laughing and side hugging him. This has thoroughly turned me sour against this establishment, and the group I have been with. After two attempts to impress my concerns to the manager on duty, with no response, I have given up on any good thoughts on this place.. and will not return.
